author: Lauren Murphy
title: MusicNews | Jess Glynne will play Dublin's Olympia Theatre next March
text:
She enjoyed huge success providing the vocals on hits by Clean Bandit and Route 94, but Londoner Jess Glynne proved herself more than capable with her solo debut album 'I Cry When I Laugh ' earlier this year.
Now, the pop singer will take to the road to promote it, and her forthcoming tour includes a date at Dublin's Olympia Theatre next year.
She'll play the venue on March 31st, 2016.
Tickets are from â‚¬28.60 including booking fee, and on sale from usual outlets this Friday at 9am.
